value.value: The alpha-linolenic acid content in the essential oils present in or extracted from a plant or the plant part such as seed.

definition.value: According to the Codex Alimentarium, the FAO international standards for food product specifications, the normal values may differ depending on the source plant. For example, in soybean oil the normal values for alpha-linolenic acid content are 4.5% - 11%.

value.value: An assay to determine the sensitivity (tolerance or susceptibility) exhibited by a plant or a group of plants (population) towards the applied herbicide glyphosate.

definition.value: It is expected that the herbicide application must not affect the agronomic yield, if any.
